Indication in the context of respiratory conditions. 
 Plantago lanceolata is indicated for symptoms of respiratory disease, namely cough, pharyngitis, and fever (
 CHILE, 2010). Other indications include as demulcent, to reduce bronchial catarrh and mild inflammation of the pharynx (
 Blumenthal et al., 1998; 
 ESCOP, 2003b; 
 Wichtl, 2004; 
 Boskabady et al., 2006a).
